51SIMPLEQ_HEAD(nouveau_pci_task_head, nouveau_pci_task);
52
53struct nouveau_pci_softc {
54 device_t sc_dev;
55 struct pci_attach_args sc_pa;
56 enum {
57 NOUVEAU_TASK_ATTACH,
58 NOUVEAU_TASK_WORKQUEUE,
59 } sc_task_state;
60 union {
61 struct workqueue *workqueue;
62 struct nouveau_pci_task_head attach;
63 } sc_task_u;
64 struct drm_device *sc_drm_dev;
65 struct pci_dev sc_pci_dev;
66 struct nvkm_device *sc_nv_dev;
67};

85static int
86nouveau_pci_match(device_t parent, cfdata_t match, void *aux)
87{
88 const struct pci_attach_args *const pa = aux;
89 struct pci_dev pdev;
90 struct nvkm_device *device;
91 int ret;
92
93 if (PCI_VENDOR(pa->pa_id) != PCI_VENDOR_NVIDIA &&
94 PCI_VENDOR(pa->pa_id) != PCI_VENDOR_NVIDIA_SGS)
95 return 0;
96
97 if (PCI_CLASS(pa->pa_class) != PCI_CLASS_DISPLAY)
98 return 0;
99
100#define IS_BETWEEN(x,y) \
101 (PCI_PRODUCT(pa->pa_id) >= (x) && PCI_PRODUCT(pa->pa_id) <= (y))
102 /*
103 * NetBSD drm2 doesn't support Pascal, Volta or Turing based cards:
104 * 0x1580-0x15ff GP100
105 * 0x1b00-0x1b7f GP102
106 * 0x1b80-0x1bff GP104
107 * 0x1c00-0x1c7f GP106
108 * 0x1c80-0x1cff GP107
109 * 0x1d00-0x1d7f GP108
110 * 0x1d80-0x1dff GV100
111 * 0x1e00-0x1e7f TU102
112 * 0x1e80-0x1eff TU104
113 * 0x1f00-0x1f7f TU106
114 */
115
116 if (IS_BETWEEN(0x1580, 0x15ff) ||
117 IS_BETWEEN(0x1b00, 0x1b7f) ||
118 IS_BETWEEN(0x1b80, 0x1bff) ||
119 IS_BETWEEN(0x1c00, 0x1c7f) ||
120 IS_BETWEEN(0x1c80, 0x1cff) ||
121 IS_BETWEEN(0x1d00, 0x1d7f) ||
122 IS_BETWEEN(0x1d80, 0x1dff) ||
123 IS_BETWEEN(0x1e00, 0x1e7f) ||
124 IS_BETWEEN(0x1e80, 0x1eff) ||
125 IS_BETWEEN(0x1f00, 0x1f7f))
126 return 0;
127#undef IS_BETWEEN
128
129 linux_pci_dev_init(&pdev, parent /* XXX bogus */, parent, pa, 0);
130 ret = nvkm_device_pci_new(&pdev, NULL, "error",
131 /* detect */ true, /* mmio */ false, /* subdev_mask */ 0, &device);
132 if (ret == 0) /* don't want to hang onto it */
133 nvkm_device_del(&device);
134 linux_pci_dev_destroy(&pdev);
135 if (ret) /* failure */
136 return 0;
137
138 return 6; /* XXX Beat genfb_pci... */
139}

141extern char *nouveau_config;
142extern char *nouveau_debug;
143
144static void
145nouveau_pci_attach(device_t parent, device_t self, void *aux)
146{
147 struct nouveau_pci_softc *const sc = device_private(self);
148 const struct pci_attach_args *const pa = aux;
149
150 pci_aprint_devinfo(pa, NULL);
151
152 if (!pmf_device_register(self, &nouveau_pci_suspend, &nouveau_pci_resume))
153 aprint_error_dev(self, "unable to establish power handler\n");
154
155 /*
156 * Trivial initialization first; the rest will come after we
157 * have mounted the root file system and can load firmware
158 * images.
159 */
160 sc->sc_dev = NULL;
161 sc->sc_pa = *pa;
162
163 config_mountroot(self, &nouveau_pci_attach_real);
164}
165
166static void
167nouveau_pci_attach_real(device_t self)
168{
169 struct nouveau_pci_softc *const sc = device_private(self);
170 const struct pci_attach_args *const pa = &sc->sc_pa;
171 int error;
172
173 sc->sc_dev = self;
174 sc->sc_task_state = NOUVEAU_TASK_ATTACH;
175 SIMPLEQ_INIT(&sc->sc_task_u.attach);
176
177 /* Initialize the Linux PCI device descriptor. */
178 linux_pci_dev_init(&sc->sc_pci_dev, self, device_parent(self), pa, 0);
179
180 /* XXX errno Linux->NetBSD */
181 error = -nvkm_device_pci_new(&sc->sc_pci_dev,
182 nouveau_config, nouveau_debug,
183 /* detect */ true, /* mmio */ true, /* subdev_mask */ ~0ULL,
184 &sc->sc_nv_dev);
185 if (error) {
186 aprint_error_dev(self, "unable to create nouveau device: %d\n",
187 error);
188 return;
189 }
190
191 /* XXX errno Linux->NetBSD */
192 error = -drm_pci_attach(self, pa, &sc->sc_pci_dev,
193 nouveau_drm_driver_pci, 0, &sc->sc_drm_dev);
194 if (error) {
195 aprint_error_dev(self, "unable to attach drm: %d\n", error);
196 return;
197 }
198
199 while (!SIMPLEQ_EMPTY(&sc->sc_task_u.attach)) {
200 struct nouveau_pci_task *const task =
201 SIMPLEQ_FIRST(&sc->sc_task_u.attach);
202
203 SIMPLEQ_REMOVE_HEAD(&sc->sc_task_u.attach, nt_u.queue);
204 (*task->nt_fn)(task);
205 }
206
207 sc->sc_task_state = NOUVEAU_TASK_WORKQUEUE;
208 error = workqueue_create(&sc->sc_task_u.workqueue, "nouveau_pci",
209 &nouveau_pci_task_work, NULL, PRI_NONE, IPL_NONE, WQ_MPSAFE);
210 if (error) {
211 aprint_error_dev(self, "unable to create workqueue: %d\n",
212 error);
213 sc->sc_task_u.workqueue = NULL;
214 return;
215 }
216}
217
218static int
219nouveau_pci_detach(device_t self, int flags)
220{
221 struct nouveau_pci_softc *const sc = device_private(self);
222 int error;
223
224 if (sc->sc_dev == NULL)
225 /* Not done attaching. */
226 return EBUSY;
227
228 /* XXX Check for in-use before tearing it all down... */
229 error = config_detach_children(self, flags);
230 if (error)
231 return error;
232
233 if (sc->sc_task_state == NOUVEAU_TASK_ATTACH)
234 goto out0;
235 if (sc->sc_task_u.workqueue != NULL) {
236 workqueue_destroy(sc->sc_task_u.workqueue);
237 sc->sc_task_u.workqueue = NULL;
238 }
239
240 if (sc->sc_nv_dev == NULL)
241 goto out0;
242
243 if (sc->sc_drm_dev == NULL)
244 goto out1;
245 /* XXX errno Linux->NetBSD */
246 error = -drm_pci_detach(sc->sc_drm_dev, flags);
247 if (error)
248 /* XXX Kinda too late to fail now... */
249 return error;
250 sc->sc_drm_dev = NULL;
251
252out1: nvkm_device_del(&sc->sc_nv_dev);
253out0: linux_pci_dev_destroy(&sc->sc_pci_dev);
254 pmf_device_deregister(self);
255 return 0;
256}

258/*
259 * XXX Synchronize with nouveau_do_suspend in nouveau_drm.c.
260 */
261static bool
262nouveau_pci_suspend(device_t self, const pmf_qual_t *qual __unused)
263{
264 struct nouveau_pci_softc *const sc = device_private(self);
265
266 return nouveau_pmops_suspend(sc->sc_drm_dev) == 0;
267}
268
269static bool
270nouveau_pci_resume(device_t self, const pmf_qual_t *qual)
271{
272 struct nouveau_pci_softc *const sc = device_private(self);
273
274 return nouveau_pmops_resume(sc->sc_drm_dev) == 0;
275}
276
277static void
278nouveau_pci_task_work(struct work *work, void *cookie __unused)
279{
280 struct nouveau_pci_task *const task = container_of(work,
281 struct nouveau_pci_task, nt_u.work);
282
283 (*task->nt_fn)(task);
284}
285
286int
287nouveau_pci_task_schedule(device_t self, struct nouveau_pci_task *task)
288{
289 struct nouveau_pci_softc *const sc = device_private(self);
290
291 switch (sc->sc_task_state) {
292 case NOUVEAU_TASK_ATTACH:
293 SIMPLEQ_INSERT_TAIL(&sc->sc_task_u.attach, task, nt_u.queue);
294 return 0;
295 case NOUVEAU_TASK_WORKQUEUE:
296 if (sc->sc_task_u.workqueue == NULL) {
297 aprint_error_dev(self, "unable to schedule task\n");
298 return EIO;
299 }
300 workqueue_enqueue(sc->sc_task_u.workqueue, &task->nt_u.work,
301 NULL);
302 return 0;
303 default:
304 panic("nouveau in invalid task state: %d\n",
305 (int)sc->sc_task_state);
306 }
307}

309extern struct drm_driver *const nouveau_drm_driver_stub; /* XXX */
310extern struct drm_driver *const nouveau_drm_driver_pci; /* XXX */
311
312static int
313nouveau_pci_modcmd(modcmd_t cmd, void *arg __unused)
314{
315
316 switch (cmd) {
317 case MODULE_CMD_INIT:
318 *nouveau_drm_driver_pci = *nouveau_drm_driver_stub;
319 nouveau_drm_driver_pci->set_busid = drm_pci_set_busid;
320 nouveau_drm_driver_pci->request_irq = drm_pci_request_irq;
321 nouveau_drm_driver_pci->free_irq = drm_pci_free_irq;
322#if 0 /* XXX nouveau acpi */
323 nouveau_register_dsm_handler();
324#endif
325 break;
326 case MODULE_CMD_FINI:
327#if 0 /* XXX nouveau acpi */
328 nouveau_unregister_dsm_handler();
329#endif
330 break;
331 default:
332 return ENOTTY;
333 }
334
335 return 0;
336}
